Title : Seymour Joseph Guy
Text : [[File:Seymour Joseph Guy - Unconscious of Danger - Google Art Project.jpg|thumb|right|Unconscious of Danger]]
'''Seymour Joseph Guy''' (1824&ndash;1910), was an American romance painter.

==Biography==
He was born and trained in London but moved to New York City, where he is known for genre works.<ref name=RKD>[http://explore.rkd.nl/nl/artists/34762 Seymour Joseph Guy] in the [[RKD]]</ref> He trained for four years with the portrait painter [[Ambrosini Jerôme]] and married the daughter of an engraver, Anna Maria Barber, before his move to New York in 1854.<ref name=AAG>[http://americanartgallery.org/artist/readmore/id/819 Seymour Joseph Guy] in the American Art gallery</ref> He was a member of the Sketch club and became friends with [[John George Brown]], and they both began to paint genre works of children, probably inspired by their own, as Guy eventually had nine.<ref name=AAG/>
He died at his home in New York on December 10, 1910.<ref>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VMBBAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA312#v=onepage&q&f=false | title=American Art Annual, Volume 9 | publisher=MacMillan Company | year=1911 | pages=312}}</ref>

